  "prompt": "My ca ipcc score is 194 is there any possibility of hike in score after revaluation?",
  "response": "In the CA IPCC (Integrated Professional Competence Course) examination, revaluation can lead to a change in your score if there were any mistakes in the evaluation of your answer sheets. However, the possibility of a score increase after revaluation depends on various factors, including the marking scheme, your performance in the exams, and whether there were any errors in the grading process.\n\nIf you believe that your answers were marked incorrectly or that you deserve additional marks based on your responses, you may consider applying for revaluation. However, it's important to keep in mind that not all revaluations result in an increase in score; some may even stay the same or decrease if discrepancies are found.\n\nCheck the official guidelines from the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) regarding the revaluation process, deadlines, and procedures. Ultimately, the decision about whether your score will increase can only be determined after the revaluation is completed.",
